			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I see, but...<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Quietust wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Next question?</div><br />...why does a chip with a pin clearly named "/CE" (EPROM, Flash ROM) work when used in place of the Nintendo ROM (which supposedly has a +CE pin)?<br /><br />Sorry if I'm being annoying over this, but this can't be right. You can't connect /A13 to /CE and expect the chip to be enabled when accessing memory below $2000.</div>
<br />
<br />Because the Nintendo ROM doesn't have a +CE pin - it has a /CE pin which is connected to A13. /A13 <strong>is not used</strong> for CHR ROM (only nametable RAM), which is why I said that said document is <strong>wrong</strong>.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
